    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Maginot Line in the Sky</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tim Walter letter says missile defense system is $60 billion boondoggle (July 9 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Key Missile Parts Are Left Untested as Booster Fails'' (front page, July 9):</p>
        <p>Not only did the ''Son of Star Wars'' interceptor missile fail, and not only can Mylar balloons and other objects decoy it, but such a system is also a Maginot Line in the sky to start with.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Key Missile Parts Are Left Untested as Booster Fails'' (front page, July 9):</p>
        <p>Not only did the ''Son of Star Wars'' interceptor missile fail, and not only can Mylar balloons and other objects decoy it, but such a system is also a Maginot Line in the sky to start with.</p>
        <p>A cruise missile could fly under it, and an S.U.V. with a nuclear bomb could destroy any city.</p>
        <p>This $60 billion boondoggle serves only military contractors and the recipients of their campaign contributions.</p>
        <p>TIM WALTER  Lee, Mass., July 9, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
